{
  "texts": [
    "Results are reported on the Occ3D-nuScenes dataset [39] without using the visibility mask for training, under a real-time inference setting (≤100 ms).",
    "MethodRayIoU RayIoU1m RayIoU2m RayIoU4m SpaseOcc [30] 35.1 29.1 35.8 40.3 GSD-Occ [8] 38.9 33.0 39.7 44.1 ODG [35] 39.2 ---OPUS [40] 40.3 33.7 41.1 46.0 DuOcc (Ours) 41.1 34.2 41.9 47.1 RayIoU (41.1), consistently outperforming prior real-time approaches.",
    "Together, these results demonstrate that DuOcc provides state-of-the-art accuracy while maintaining practical runtime and memory efficiency, making it practical for real-world deployment.Qualitative results in Fig. 4 also demonstrate that DuOcc more precisely reconstructs the surrounding environment compared to the previous state-of-the-art real-time method GSD-Occ [8], yielding clearer representations of dynamic objects (Rows 1-2) and static structures (Row 3).",
    "Effect of StreamAgg ComponentsTab.",
    "5 shows the effect of each component in StreamAgg.Motion-aware Warping provides the fundamental improvement by aligning voxel features across frames, while adding RefineNet further mitigates warping artifacts, boosting performance to 39.84 mIoU."
